text.data-name: OUR NEXT CHAPTER In 2004, we set out to build a company that w
text.tspan: In 2004, we set out to build a company that would be uniquely suited to help brands thrive in contemporary culture. From the beginning, Translation was a different kind of team: a diverse mix of music industry veterans, strategic experts, multidisciplinary creatives, and innovative business leaders.

Over the years, the Translation team has worked on a creative canvas as broad as culture itself: partnering with clients in creating not just advertising but everything from the fourth biggest music festival in America to full-length documentary films to TV shows that we’ve sold to networks to a line of sneakers inspired by a fictitious insurance agent. And we’ve been privileged to work with some of the world’s most ambitious brands including State Farm, the NBA, Apple Music, the NFL, and dozens more.

Knowing that cultural relevance demands constant re-invention, we have gone through countless transformations as we have seen our Agency grow from a few people gathered in a single conference room to a vibrant team of 150 across two coasts.
And now, in partnership with Alphabet Inc., Andreessen Horowitz, 21st Century Fox and Floodgate, we are embarking upon our greatest transformation to date.
We are thrilled to introduce UnitedMasters: Translation’s new partner company.

UnitedMasters is an entirely new kind of music company, built to unite the power of data and the pursuit of creative freedom to invent new ways to help artists maximize their creative and economic potential.

We believe the combination of Translation and UnitedMasters will enable us to combine storytelling, culture, and technology to re-invent how cultural influence can create value for both brands and artists. This is the biggest chapter yet of the story we began in 2004, and we couldn’t be more excited about what the future will hold.
